1
00:00:14,467 --> 00:00:15,767
<i> You have no shame!</i>

2
00:00:18,033 --> 00:00:19,833
<i> I swear to you, Hazel.</i>

3
00:00:20,100 --> 00:00:24,333
<i>You're going to pay for
everything you did to my family.</i>

4
00:00:24,467 --> 00:00:27,267
<i>I'm willing to cooperate
with you against Hazel.</i>

5
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:30,633
<i>This will help my family finally
get justice.</i>

6
00:00:30,767 --> 00:00:33,033
<i>Just because you're cooperating</i>

7
00:00:33,167 --> 00:00:34,067
<i>doesn't mean you're off
the hook.</i>

8
00:00:34,233 --> 00:00:38,133
<i>You still have to answer
for what you did.</i>

9
00:00:38,267 --> 00:00:42,100
<i>I was the one who gave Hazel
Jeffrey's flight details.</i>

10
00:00:42,233 --> 00:00:45,567
<i>I was also involved
in Joel's death.</i>

11
00:00:46,933 --> 00:00:48,067
<i> Felma, why?</i>

12
00:00:48,300 --> 00:00:52,033
<i>It's just like what we went
through before with Coleen.</i>

13
00:00:52,167 --> 00:00:54,100
<i>What if Hazel does something
again?</i>

14
00:00:54,367 --> 00:00:55,733
<i> Felma, don't worry.</i>

15
00:00:55,867 --> 00:00:58,433
<i>I promise you,
Hazel will go to prison.</i>

16
00:00:58,567 --> 00:01:02,200
<i>Jessica, I'm so happy you
showed me what it feels like</i>

17
00:01:02,333 --> 00:01:04,233
<i> to have a little sister.</i>

18
00:01:04,367 --> 00:01:07,767
<i>Thank you for taking care
of Dad on our behalf.</i>

19
00:01:07,933 --> 00:01:13,567
<i>I wish you were here to see that
we're whole again as a family.</i>

20
00:01:13,833 --> 00:01:18,667
<i>Thank you for treating me
like your second mother.</i>

21
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:21,033
<i>I'll never forget you, Jessica.</i>

22
00:01:21,167 --> 00:01:23,333
<i> I love you so much, my child.</i>

23
00:01:23,467 --> 00:01:24,733
<i> You monster!</i>

24
00:01:24,867 --> 00:01:25,467
<i> Coward!</i>

25
00:01:25,600 --> 00:01:26,800
<i> You're the coward!</i>

26
00:01:27,033 --> 00:01:28,633
<i>Because you can't admit
to yourself</i>

27
00:01:28,767 --> 00:01:30,433
<i> how horrible you are!</i>

28
00:01:30,567 --> 00:01:33,167
<i>Maybe it's right that we lost
our child.</i>

29
00:01:33,300 --> 00:01:36,067
<i>Because you were never capable
of being a good mother!</i>

30
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:37,733
<i> You're disgusting!</i>

31
00:01:37,867 --> 00:01:39,267
<i>- You have no shame!
- Move it! Let's go!</i>

32
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:41,000
<i> Rot in jail!</i>

33
00:02:27,967 --> 00:02:28,900
Jessica,

34
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:32,633
I just have one last wish.

35
00:02:34,300 --> 00:02:37,100
Maybe you could visit me
in my dreams.

36
00:02:38,300 --> 00:02:40,500
I just want to see you again.

37
00:02:42,067 --> 00:02:47,567
And I want you to see me
walking again.

38
00:02:58,733 --> 00:03:00,333
<i> Jessica...</i>

39
00:03:00,467 --> 00:03:01,667
<i> Jessica, my child?</i>

40
00:03:03,467 --> 00:03:05,200
<i> I love you, Dad.</i>

41
00:03:05,333 --> 00:03:06,733
<i> I love you more, sweetheart.</i>

42
00:03:08,067 --> 00:03:09,933
<i> Jessica, wait.</i>

43
00:03:10,067 --> 00:03:11,633
<i> Come here, sweetheart.</i>

44
00:03:11,767 --> 00:03:13,367
<i> Let me hug you.</i>

45
00:03:14,867 --> 00:03:16,467
<i> Just once.</i>

46
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:37,500
Thank you so, so much, Jessica.

47
00:03:39,567 --> 00:03:41,467
I love you so much, my child.

48
00:03:52,833 --> 00:03:53,833
Come in.

49
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:01,267
Manuel, you're already awake.

50
00:04:01,533 --> 00:04:03,600
Attorney Yeban is waiting
for you.

51
00:04:05,367 --> 00:04:07,367
Did you dream about Jessica?

52
00:04:13,533 --> 00:04:19,500
Attorney Yeban, do you think
Hazel can get away with this?

53
00:04:20,167 --> 00:04:21,033
Well...

54
00:04:21,167 --> 00:04:23,400
Jeffrey's testimony is strong.

55
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:28,367
Especially since it's backed up
by Jojo's statements.

56
00:04:29,900 --> 00:04:33,333
If their stories stay
consistent,

57
00:04:33,467 --> 00:04:37,633
and all the affidavits
and documents match,

58
00:04:37,900 --> 00:04:42,700
Hazel will have a hard time
escaping justice.

59
00:04:42,833 --> 00:04:47,533
We just need to make sure Jojo
doesn't back out.

60
00:04:47,667 --> 00:04:49,300
To make sure we win.

61
00:04:49,433 --> 00:04:54,467
Felma, that's why we're here.
To make sure he doesn't.

62
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:57,100
That's what's been
bothering me, too.

63
00:04:57,400 --> 00:04:59,267
Jojo was involved.

64
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:01,167
He was an accomplice.

65
00:05:01,333 --> 00:05:04,833
The law recognizes degrees
of participation.

66
00:05:04,967 --> 00:05:11,367
Based on the evidence we have,
he's not the main offender.

67
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:14,833
He surrendered, reported Hazel,

68
00:05:14,967 --> 00:05:17,967
and most importantly,
he saved Jeffrey.

69
00:05:18,100 --> 00:05:20,000
If not for him,

70
00:05:21,267 --> 00:05:23,333
our eldest son might be dead.

71
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:26,933
Yes, and that is legally
significant.

72
00:05:27,233 --> 00:05:30,533
The justice system doesn't treat
all defendants the same.

73
00:05:32,267 --> 00:05:35,733
He might even qualify
as a state witness.

74
00:05:35,900 --> 00:05:39,300
Attorney,
what about Hazel's people?

75
00:05:40,767 --> 00:05:44,633
That's the gap we still need
to fill.

76
00:05:44,767 --> 00:05:47,200
I know two of Hazel's men,

77
00:05:47,333 --> 00:05:49,433
Anton and Nando.

78
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:51,700
But I don't know
their last names.

79
00:05:53,067 --> 00:05:55,867
There's another one who's really
close to Hazel,

80
00:05:57,367 --> 00:05:58,867
but I've never seen him.

81
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:01,267
Jojo,

82
00:06:03,100 --> 00:06:05,167
that's not the only reason
we came.

83
00:06:06,667 --> 00:06:10,600
We also wanted to ask you
not to...

84
00:06:10,767 --> 00:06:12,467
Ma'am...

85
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:14,933
I'm a man of my word.

86
00:06:15,067 --> 00:06:18,100
I won't change or take back
my statements.

87
00:06:19,367 --> 00:06:21,100
Thank you.

88
00:06:21,367 --> 00:06:23,900
There's nothing to thank me for.

89
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:26,500
I'm just making things right.

90
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:29,900
Excuse me.

91
00:06:30,033 --> 00:06:31,767
I just need to make a call.

92
00:06:38,733 --> 00:06:40,933
What about Alice, Jojo?

93
00:06:41,100 --> 00:06:42,900
I know her, Attorney.

94
00:06:43,167 --> 00:06:46,133
But she's loyal to Hazel.

95
00:06:46,367 --> 00:06:48,367
She won't turn on her.

96
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:51,033
Alice has had enough, too, Sir.

97
00:06:51,167 --> 00:06:53,900
Hazel used her and fooled her.

98
00:06:54,200 --> 00:06:56,400
She had nothing to do
with Hazel's crimes.

99
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:17,567
What are you doing here again?

100
00:07:19,367 --> 00:07:20,433
Nothing.

101
00:07:21,633 --> 00:07:23,200
I just wanted to see you...

102
00:07:24,467 --> 00:07:27,300
one last time.

103
00:07:29,333 --> 00:07:32,100
Don't be stupid, Felma.

104
00:07:32,233 --> 00:07:36,733
We'll see each other in court,
and I'll still beat you.

105
00:07:36,867 --> 00:07:39,567
Two things, Hazel.

106
00:07:39,700 --> 00:07:40,800
First,

107
00:07:42,633 --> 00:07:45,333
I won't be attending
your hearings.

108
00:07:45,467 --> 00:07:49,100
Why would I waste my time
on you?

109
00:07:49,267 --> 00:07:51,033
Second,

110
00:07:51,333 --> 00:07:56,833
you'll lose with all the charges
we filed against you.

111
00:08:01,133 --> 00:08:06,400
You'll pay for every sin you
committed against my family.

112
00:08:06,533 --> 00:08:09,467
You'll spend the rest
of your life in prison.

113
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:12,033
And we'll forget you.

114
00:08:12,167 --> 00:08:17,000
I'll make sure our family never
speaks your name again.

115
00:08:18,300 --> 00:08:23,067
Even mentioning you
will be forbidden.

116
00:08:24,967 --> 00:08:26,400
Until...

117
00:08:28,900 --> 00:08:33,967
no one even remembers
who you are.

118
00:08:34,100 --> 00:08:37,600
You'll disappear from our world.

119
00:08:37,733 --> 00:08:40,833
You'll be nothing but filth,

120
00:08:42,367 --> 00:08:47,033
a stain that once touched
my family.

121
00:08:54,267 --> 00:08:55,933
Don't worry.

122
00:08:56,067 --> 00:08:57,533
I won't spit on you.

123
00:08:57,667 --> 00:08:59,900
You're not worth my saliva.

124
00:09:01,833 --> 00:09:03,667
I'm just going back
to the person

125
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:06,033
who will witness against you.

126
00:09:06,167 --> 00:09:07,567
You animal, Felma!

127
00:09:07,700 --> 00:09:09,667
Felma, come back here!

128
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:12,100
We're not done yet, you animal!

129
00:09:15,267 --> 00:09:17,267
Thank you so much, Jojo.

130
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:18,400
- Thank you.
- Thank you, too, Sir.

131
00:09:18,533 --> 00:09:20,233
Attorney, thank you.

132
00:09:21,367 --> 00:09:24,867
Thank you.

133
00:09:30,167 --> 00:09:31,233
Thank you very much.

134
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:36,767
Jojo, wait a second.

135
00:09:39,667 --> 00:09:42,567
This is my favorite photo
of Jessica.

136
00:09:43,967 --> 00:09:47,367
Please take care of it the way
I did for almost twenty years.

137
00:09:48,700 --> 00:09:50,067
It's the only copy.

138
00:10:04,500 --> 00:10:05,533
How about you?

139
00:10:07,233 --> 00:10:08,533
Don't worry about me.

140
00:10:10,033 --> 00:10:12,067
You don't have memories
of Jessica.

141
00:10:14,967 --> 00:10:16,000
I have plenty.

142
00:10:23,067 --> 00:10:24,300
We're heading out.

143
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:39,667
Come on, let's celebrate.

144
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:42,867
Wait, I'll call the kids, okay?

145
00:10:43,867 --> 00:10:45,533
So they can join us.

146
00:10:47,100 --> 00:10:50,967
Sir Manuel and I already
have plans, Ma'am.

147
00:10:51,100 --> 00:10:52,233
Where to?

148
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:57,400
After we drop you off,
we're going to the RTC.

149
00:10:57,533 --> 00:11:00,200
To file the annulment against
Hazel.

150
00:11:00,333 --> 00:11:02,067
Felma, just a little longer.

151
00:11:02,367 --> 00:11:03,767
I'll finally be free from Hazel.

152
00:11:05,067 --> 00:11:06,267
We can finally get married.

153
00:11:08,433 --> 00:11:09,900
Yeah.

154
00:11:10,033 --> 00:11:12,367
We're filing for annulment
due to fraud.

155
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:15,167
Hazel made Sir Manuel believe

156
00:11:15,300 --> 00:11:18,500
that the child she was carrying
was his.

157
00:11:18,633 --> 00:11:19,967
There's a strong chance
the court

158
00:11:20,100 --> 00:11:22,100
will fast-track the decision.

159
00:11:22,233 --> 00:11:24,267
If you'd like,
you're welcome to come with us.

160
00:11:34,933 --> 00:11:36,300
Alice.

161
00:11:36,433 --> 00:11:37,467
Alice, thank you.

162
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:39,067
Thank you for visiting me.

163
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:43,133
I got a subpoena.

164
00:11:44,633 --> 00:11:49,633
They said there's probable cause
in the case against me.

165
00:11:49,767 --> 00:11:52,533
Alice, please help me.

166
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:55,200
Call Maximo.

167
00:11:55,333 --> 00:11:58,767
Tell him to help get me out
of here.

168
00:11:58,900 --> 00:12:01,067
Hurry. Please.

169
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:02,300
Alice.

170
00:12:03,967 --> 00:12:05,333
No, Hazel.

171
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:08,500
I'm done.

172
00:12:11,533 --> 00:12:17,133
I only came here to say goodbye.

173
00:12:22,033 --> 00:12:23,633
You're turning your back on me?

174
00:12:26,633 --> 00:12:29,100
You can't do that, Alice.

175
00:12:31,333 --> 00:12:33,667
You can't just abandon me.

176
00:12:36,900 --> 00:12:38,533
You're all I have left.

177
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:43,867
Have you forgotten everything
I did for you?

178
00:12:45,667 --> 00:12:48,967
I helped you back
in Saudi Arabia.

179
00:12:49,233 --> 00:12:52,033
Every mess you made,
I cleaned up for you.

180
00:12:52,167 --> 00:12:54,233
You forgot about it already?

181
00:12:54,367 --> 00:12:56,033
I haven't forgotten.

182
00:12:57,900 --> 00:13:00,500
But I think I've already paid
my dues.

183
00:13:00,767 --> 00:13:03,000
More than enough.

184
00:13:03,133 --> 00:13:06,367
I followed every order you
gave me.

185
00:13:08,233 --> 00:13:09,667
Even when it was wrong.

186
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:13,100
Even when I didn't want to.

187
00:13:15,700 --> 00:13:17,700
So you're really going
to betray me?

188
00:13:18,700 --> 00:13:19,833
No.

189
00:13:22,367 --> 00:13:25,333
But if the court calls me in,

190
00:13:25,467 --> 00:13:27,033
I won't have a choice.

191
00:13:27,167 --> 00:13:31,133
I'll have to tell them
everything I know.

192
00:13:33,633 --> 00:13:35,167
Alice, try it.

193
00:13:37,033 --> 00:13:39,467
Just try to turn on me,

194
00:13:39,867 --> 00:13:41,733
and you'll pay for it.

195
00:13:41,867 --> 00:13:43,067
You'd better watch yourself.

196
00:13:44,100 --> 00:13:46,433
What are you going to do?

197
00:13:46,567 --> 00:13:47,733
Drag me down with you?

198
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:51,167
You don't have any evidence
against me!

199
00:13:51,900 --> 00:13:54,000
You monster!

200
00:13:54,133 --> 00:13:55,100
Monster!

201
00:13:55,267 --> 00:13:55,900
No!

202
00:13:56,567 --> 00:13:58,333
Come back here!
Don't leave me!

203
00:13:58,867 --> 00:14:00,533
Alice!

204
00:14:00,667 --> 00:14:01,700
You're all I...

205
00:14:01,833 --> 00:14:02,833
Alice!

206
00:14:02,967 --> 00:14:04,267
Alice!

207
00:14:08,133 --> 00:14:10,067
Please sign here,
acknowledged receipt.

208
00:14:18,567 --> 00:14:20,300
Mrs. Hazel Capistrano-Cruz...

209
00:14:21,467 --> 00:14:24,033
you've been served a summons
from the Regional Trial Court.

210
00:14:24,167 --> 00:14:25,000
Here you go.

211
00:14:34,567 --> 00:14:35,800
Annulment?

212
00:14:46,933 --> 00:14:49,133
Annulment? Annulment?

213
00:14:49,267 --> 00:14:50,733
Here! Here!

214
00:14:50,867 --> 00:14:53,833
Take it back!
Annulment!

215
00:14:59,467 --> 00:15:00,933
You animals!

216
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:03,667
All of you,
you're all in this together!

217
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:07,833
Go on! Gang up on me!

218
00:15:24,300 --> 00:15:30,600
- Happy birthday to you.
- Hey! Hey!

219
00:15:30,733 --> 00:15:33,733
- Happy birthday,
- Happy birthday,

220
00:15:33,867 --> 00:15:37,900
- Happy birthday to you!
- Happy birthday to you!

221
00:15:38,067 --> 00:15:39,300
Okay, okay,
everyone, close your eyes.

222
00:15:39,433 --> 00:15:40,533
Let's close our eyes.

223
00:15:44,167 --> 00:15:46,233
Wait, why did you
close your eyes?

224
00:15:46,367 --> 00:15:48,067
We made a wish for Mom.

225
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:49,400
Hey, me, too!

226
00:15:49,533 --> 00:15:50,300
Close them again.

227
00:15:50,433 --> 00:15:51,400
Again?

228
00:15:51,533 --> 00:15:53,600
- Oh!
- Oh, that's it.

229
00:15:53,733 --> 00:15:58,267
And for peace and a happy life
for our family.

230
00:15:58,400 --> 00:15:59,500
There.

231
00:16:00,667 --> 00:16:03,700
Happy birthday, Mom!

232
00:16:03,833 --> 00:16:05,300
Everybody says...

233
00:16:05,433 --> 00:16:08,333
- Amen!
- Amen!

234
00:16:10,033 --> 00:16:11,433
Oh, wait.

235
00:16:11,567 --> 00:16:12,967
- Who is it?
- It's Attorney Yeban.

236
00:16:13,100 --> 00:16:14,567
Attorney?

237
00:16:14,700 --> 00:16:17,133
- Hello, Attorney.
<i> - Sir Manuel.</i>

238
00:16:17,267 --> 00:16:18,300
Yes, good news.

239
00:16:18,433 --> 00:16:21,067
We already have a schedule
for the first hearing.

240
00:16:22,100 --> 00:16:24,733
That's the best birthday gift
for you, Mom.

241
00:16:24,867 --> 00:16:25,967
Don't celebrate yet.

242
00:16:26,367 --> 00:16:28,000
We still have a long road ahead.

243
00:16:28,133 --> 00:16:29,733
It could take months or years.

244
00:16:30,100 --> 00:16:32,133
Even if it takes
a decade, Attorney.

245
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:34,367
As long as Hazel never gets out
of prison.

246
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:36,833
That's right, Attorney.

247
00:16:36,967 --> 00:16:39,433
No matter how long it takes,

248
00:16:39,567 --> 00:16:42,233
what matters is that
justice is served

249
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:45,400
and no one threatens
our family again.

250
00:16:45,667 --> 00:16:49,233
Most of all,
no one gets hurt anymore.

251
00:16:49,367 --> 00:16:51,400
All right, Attorney,
thank you so much.

252
00:16:51,533 --> 00:16:52,333
Group hug!

253
00:16:52,467 --> 00:16:54,467
Happy birthday!

254
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:55,867
- Happy birthday!
- Let me join!

255
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:57,333
Didang, that's so you.

256
00:16:59,067 --> 00:17:02,300
- Happy birthday!
- Happy birthday!

257
00:18:41,567 --> 00:18:43,933
So, Manuel and Felma,

258
00:18:45,600 --> 00:18:49,000
you can speak your vows
to one another.

259
00:18:57,267 --> 00:18:58,600
Felma, my love...

260
00:19:01,633 --> 00:19:03,967
First of all,
I want to say sorry

261
00:19:04,100 --> 00:19:06,933
for all the wrong things I did.

262
00:19:08,467 --> 00:19:10,500
For all the ways I failed you.

263
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:13,133
Also when...

264
00:19:14,933 --> 00:19:17,267
the time when I neglected you.

265
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:23,100
For all the times I hurt you.

266
00:19:25,967 --> 00:19:27,533
Love, you are my world.

267
00:19:28,900 --> 00:19:30,233
You are my home.

268
00:19:31,667 --> 00:19:35,033
You are my rest when I'm tired.

269
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:38,233
My smile when I'm sad.

270
00:19:40,267 --> 00:19:42,833
You, and only you,
are the one I choose...

271
00:19:43,900 --> 00:19:45,600
to love every single day.

272
00:19:46,733 --> 00:19:47,933
You were my choice then...

273
00:19:49,433 --> 00:19:50,200
you are my choice now

274
00:19:50,333 --> 00:19:51,633
and you will be
my choice tomorrow.

275
00:19:55,567 --> 00:19:57,500
I will love you every day
of my life.

276
00:19:59,833 --> 00:20:02,267
And even after I die,
I will still love you.

277
00:20:04,467 --> 00:20:08,033
Even if we cross
into the next life...

278
00:20:10,233 --> 00:20:13,600
I will find you,
I will love you again...

279
00:20:15,933 --> 00:20:17,633
and I will marry you again.

280
00:20:24,500 --> 00:20:28,367
Felma, do you take Manuel
as your lawful...

281
00:20:28,500 --> 00:20:29,333
I do.

282
00:20:30,733 --> 00:20:32,233
It's your turn, Manuel.

283
00:20:32,367 --> 00:20:34,233
- Do you take Felma...
- I do! I do!

284
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:38,533
- I do!
- Dad's excited!

285
00:20:38,667 --> 00:20:41,500
Wait till the "you may kiss
the bride."

286
00:20:41,633 --> 00:20:42,667
Just wait, you'll see.

287
00:20:42,800 --> 00:20:44,467
Oh my! That's true!

288
00:20:44,600 --> 00:20:47,000
At this rate, they'll have
the honeymoon right here!

289
00:20:47,133 --> 00:20:48,667
- Didang!
- Hey!

290
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:51,500
Well, since you seem
to be in a hurry, Manuel...

291
00:20:51,633 --> 00:20:54,433
go ahead, kiss the bride!

292
00:20:58,167 --> 00:20:59,533
You may kiss the bride!

293
00:21:12,467 --> 00:21:13,800
My love...

294
00:21:14,100 --> 00:21:16,900
At last, I've fulfilled
my promise to you.

295
00:21:18,033 --> 00:21:19,667
To marry you.

296
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:23,767
From this day on,
you are the one.

297
00:21:24,067 --> 00:21:29,233
No, you are the only one

298
00:21:29,533 --> 00:21:31,567
and true Mrs. Cruz.

299
00:21:45,367 --> 00:21:47,667
Of course,
it's not just Mom and Dad

300
00:21:47,800 --> 00:21:49,667
who are the happiest today.

301
00:21:50,433 --> 00:21:51,967
We are, too.

302
00:21:52,100 --> 00:21:54,567
Because, finally,
our family is whole again.

303
00:21:54,700 --> 00:21:55,867
- Yes!
- Yes!

304
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:01,900
Our family has been through
so much.

305
00:22:02,033 --> 00:22:04,767
Sadness, anger and pain.

306
00:22:05,800 --> 00:22:08,800
But all of that was erased
by love.

307
00:22:08,933 --> 00:22:10,167
And by forgiveness.

308
00:22:14,233 --> 00:22:16,600
So, Mom, Dad...

309
00:22:16,767 --> 00:22:20,067
Thank you for never giving up
on each other.

310
00:22:20,433 --> 00:22:23,000
And because of this new love
you've found,

311
00:22:23,267 --> 00:22:27,500
we're excited for the new
chapter of our lives!

312
00:22:30,167 --> 00:22:31,633
And as for me,

313
00:22:31,767 --> 00:22:32,933
I just want to say

314
00:22:33,067 --> 00:22:35,000
you look so beautiful,
Mama Pretty!

315
00:22:35,133 --> 00:22:37,333
And you look so handsome,
Papa Handsome!

316
00:22:37,467 --> 00:22:39,700
- That's true!
- That's my kid, that's my kid.

317
00:22:41,100 --> 00:22:44,767
Auntie, Uncle, you showed us
that even when you've been hurt,

318
00:22:44,900 --> 00:22:46,833
you can still choose to love.

319
00:22:49,067 --> 00:22:49,900
Ouch!

320
00:22:50,033 --> 00:22:52,333
So does that mean
you and Jepoy are next?

321
00:22:53,533 --> 00:22:56,167
Jepoy can answer that.

322
00:22:56,300 --> 00:22:57,367
Once Mom and Dad
leave that table,

323
00:22:57,500 --> 00:22:58,733
we'll take their seats next.

324
00:23:03,033 --> 00:23:04,967
You won't win, Flirty Felma.

325
00:23:06,633 --> 00:23:09,000
You think we're done?
You're wrong.

326
00:23:10,067 --> 00:23:12,400
Get ready
because I'm coming for you.

327
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:23,100
There we go!

328
00:23:23,233 --> 00:23:25,133
One, two, three!

329
00:23:26,800 --> 00:23:27,900
Everyone, get out!

330
00:23:28,033 --> 00:23:28,900
Dad, where's Mom!

331
00:23:29,033 --> 00:23:30,867
- Go ahead!
- We're not leaving without Mom!

332
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:32,533
- Where's Mom?
- Go! Get out now!

333
00:23:34,267 --> 00:23:35,733
Help!
